bug.short_desc: Numix theme messes up the desktop icons in Xfce
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1233250 Screenshot of glitchy desktop icons
The icons in the Xfce desktop look glitchy when using the Numix gtk theme installed from the Fedora package manager.
To reproduce the problem:
1. Use Xfce desktop (I tested using the Xfce spin of Fedora 25) 2. Install numix-gtk-theme from the package manager 3. Select the Numix theme under Settings->Appearance->Style
After this, the icons in the desktop start behaving strangely. The folder names appear shifted to the left, while leaving behind a shadow in the place they should be in. If I move an icon in the desktop the icon and the text shadow move correctly but some of the folder name ends up left behind in the old location. The left behind part stays that way until I switch workspaces.
The attached screenshot was taken after I moved the "Home" and "numix-gtk-theme" folders a bit to the right.
Additional info:
- I did not encounter this issue when using the MATE desktop. I haven't tested on GNOME, LXDE or Cinnamon so I don't know if they are also affected or if this is Xfce specific.
- I did not encounter this issue when I used the latest version of the Numix GTK theme from the upstream git repository.

Hi Hugo
thanks for the bug, the bug should be solved by a more recent numix-gtk-theme. The package update has been created and should hit the update channel withn 7 days.
Kind regards Sascha
